
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-herbert-simple-sr-00.txt'>
    <title>"Simple Segment Routing Header", Tom Herbert</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-herbert-simple-sr-00.txt</link>
    <description>This specification defines a simple extension header format for Segment Routing based on the current definition of the Segment Routing extension header defined for IPv6. A Segment Identifier type field is added so that the segment list might contain values other than IPv6 addresses. Optional TLVs in the segment routing header are eliminated; Destination options that precede the routing header are sufficient. Two new destination options are defined: one for Routing header security and another to specify that certain destinations should process certain options.</description>
    <dc:date>2019-03-11T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
